<h2>Information regarding reporting: Reporting not required</h2>
<p><strong><em>Reporting is not required if:</em></strong></p>
<p>The client is 17 years of age or has ever been married</p>
<p>Abuse involving divorced minors under 17, is not required to be reported under Family Code &#167;261.101. </p>
<p>If the minor's partner is not more than three years older than the pregnant minor and there is no evidence of duress, force, or threat of force and there is no indication of any other type of abuse or neglect, no report is required. If you decide not to make any report, the reason should be documented. </p>
<p>See the following information on affirmative defense.</p>
<p>DFPS can always be contacted for guidance.</p>

